We need a different feed Algorithm in #Amethyst. The separation between "New Threads" and "Conversation" is not nuanced enough and no longer suitable for its purpose. It needs to evolve, and I believe we can learn from Twitter in this domain. The goal is to merge the two feeds into a single feed.

I am in favour of displaying the feed as a pruned tree, with the root and some sub-nodes:
A) There is value in seeing replies from accounts I follow directly in my feed.
B) Similarly, there is value in seeing replies with a high number of impressions, even if I don't follow the account.

We should provide users with the freedom to configure their feed parameters. For example:

- Show replies from accounts I follow (yes/no)
- Show all replies with an impression score of x or greater (the score can be calculated based on the number of views, replies, sats received, etc.)
- Always show the note replied to (yes/no)
- Show the full note "path" to the root note (yes/no)
- And so on.
